Guild Levels and Advancement
Unique assassination marks are the only way a Ninja raises guild level.
The <Training Master> assigns an incomplete mark, with suggested level used
to favor an appropriate target rather than block advancement. Kill the exact
assigned target yourself, then use <bloody> to dip the assigned <kunai> in
the corpse's blood and give it to Yagyu. Each unique completion raises guild
level once, to a maximum of 50.

Each assignment includes one free "reroll challenge". The replacement is a
different incomplete mark, and the rejected mark returns to the future pool.
A reroll never costs GXP, rank, or training sessions. Ask Yagyu to "list
challenge" to review the current assignment and progress.
